Marvel Studios has paid tribute to Hollywood star actor, Chadwick Boseman, on Monday August 31. Recall that the actor passed away after battling colon cancer. Following the announcement of the death of Boseman, who played king T’Challa in Black Panther, much-loved superheroes for Marvel Studios took to social media to express grief at the death of the ‘Black Panther’ star. The official Twitter handle of Marvel Studio then released a video, showing Chadwick Boseman’s journey and it was an emotional one that pulled at Twitter users’ heartstrings. “You will always be our King,” read the caption. Watch the video below: You will always be our King. A post shared by  Marvel Studios (@marvelstudios) on Aug 30, 2020 at 8:06pm PDT Source Long before the advent of ‘Black Panther’, Marvel’s 2018 superhero film, which had starred the now regrettably deceased Chadwick Boseman as its lead character, many would argue out the prejudices among US filmmakers regarding the diversity of their movie casts and the descriptions for roles often accorded people of African… August 30, 2020 In "Entertainment" Boseman and Harris at a 2018 event for Families Belong Together, a coalition against separation of children who have immigrated to the U.S. from their families By Harrison Arubu New York - U.S. Democratic Party presidential candidate, Joe Biden, and his running mate, Kamala Harris, have reacted to the shocking death… August 29, 2020 In "News" By Harrison Arubu New York - Hollywood actor, Chadwick Boseman, who played King T’Challa in the 2018 American superhero movie, “Black Panther,” is dead, aged 43. He died in Los Angeles, California, on Friday evening after a four-year battle with colon cancer, his family said in a statement on his… August 29, 2020 In "Top Stories"